'''Mounir Sabet''' (sometimes spelled '''Mounir Thabet''') ({{Lang-ar|<U+0645><U+0646><U+064A><U+0631> <U+062B><U+0627><U+0628><U+062A>}}) (born 29 October 1936)<ref name="IOC">{{Cite web |url=http://www.olympic.org/en/content/The-IOC/Members/General-Mounir-SABET/ |title=General Mounir Sabet |publisher=Official website of the Olympic Movement |accessdate=2010-10-07}}</ref> is an [[Egypt]]ian [[General officer|general]] and sports official.

Born in the [[Upper Egypt]]ian city of [[Qena]], Mounir Sabet is the son of Saleh Sabet, an Egyptian [[Pediatrics|pediatrician]], and his [[Welsh people|Welsh]] wife Lily May Palmer.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.egy.com/historica/egyptianconsorts.shtml |title=Egypt's First Ladies |first=Samir |last=Raafat |month=March |year=2005 |publisher=Egy.com |accessdate=2010-10-07}}</ref> Mounir Sabet's sister [[Suzanne Mubarak|Suzanne]] is the wife of Egyptian president [[Hosni Mubarak]], and thus the current [[First Lady]] of Egypt.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Deadly Checkmate |author=Hays, Kathleen |author2=Morris, Valerie |author3=Willis, Gerri |url=http://www.accessmylibrary.com/coms2/summary_0286-19667434_ITM |format=Free with registration |agency=[[America's Intelligence Wire]] |newspaper=[[Egypt Today]] |date=10 December 2003 |accessdate=2010-10-07 |quote=the Egyptian Olympic Committee (EOC), headed by Gen. Mounir Thabet, the brother of First Lady Suzanne Mubarak...}}</ref>

Mounir Sabet was a member of the 1965 Egyptian national shooting team.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.egolympic.org.eg/en/IOC_sabet.htm |title=General Mounir Sabet |publisher=Official website of the Egyptian Olympic Committee |accessdate=2010-10-07}}</ref> He served as president of the [[Egyptian Olympic Committee]] from 1990 to 1993, and again from 1996 to 2009.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.egolympic.org.eg/ar/president_A.pdf |title=Egyptian Olympic Committee Presidents 1910 until now |publisher=Official website of the Egyptian Olympic Committee |language=Arabic |format=[[Portable Document Format|PDF]], 2.86 MB |accessdate=2010-10-07}}</ref> He has been a member of the [[International Olympic Committee]] since 1998.<ref name="IOC"/>

